Running the Code

Simply run the Python script:

```bash
python udvt_calculations.py
```

It will print all numerical predictions (relic density, masses, distortions, etc.) and optionally generate a plot of the freeze-out evolution.

Code Overview

1. Dark Matter Relic Density (relic_density)

Calculates the thermal relic abundance of the σ particle (vacuum oscillation mode) using the WIMP miracle formula.

2. Fermion Mass Hierarchy (fermion_masses)

Computes lepton and quark masses for winding numbers N=1,2,3 using exponential scaling:
m_f = κ₀ ⟨ρ⟩ e^{αN} × color_factor

3. CMB Modifications (alpha_z, thomson_cross_section, damping_tail_modification)

Models the effect of a time-varying fine-structure constant on the CMB damping tail (qualitative; full MCMC requires CLASS/CAMB).

4. Gravitational Waves from Defects

· gw_cosmic_strings – plateau from N=1 strings (PTA band)
· gw_domain_walls – peak frequency and amplitude from N=2 walls (LISA band)

5. CMB Spectral Distortions (mu_distortion, y_distortion)

Energy injection from φ → γγ decay produces μ and y distortions, within reach of PIXIE/PRISM.

6. Boltzmann Equation Solver (boltzmann_ode, solve_relic_density)

Numerical integration of the freeze-out process using scipy.integrate.odeint.

